    q_en: "How does a headers exchange work?",
    a_en: 'A headers exchange ignores routing keys and routes based on message header attributes. When binding, you specify matching rules like "department: sales" and "urgent: true" — messages only get routed if their headers match. More flexible than routing keys for complex logic but more expensive (header matching is slower than string comparison). Rarely used in practice.',
